 :tx/rationale "Create task: CE-OBSERVE: Responsive observation — every observe returns a contextual micro-hypothesis. CONTEXT: Currently 21 observations get 21 'recorded +9 datoms' responses with zero contextual insight. Dialogue is decoupled — observations during work, hypotheses at daemon startup or status check. Every framework demands continuous dialogue: Vygotsky (scaffolding IN the interaction), Popper (contradictions flagged INSTANTLY), Lacan (signifying chain extends at moment of new signifier). RATIONALE: The observe command is the agent's primary interaction point. It must be DIALOGIC, not monologic. Each observation should provoke a response that extends the signifying chain through the agent's latent space. INV-CONVERGENCE-008. APPROACH: (1) After recording observation datoms (existing), add a responsive_observation(store, new_entity, session_boundary) -> Option<MicroHypothesis> call in observe pipeline (crates/braid/src/commands/observe.rs). (2) Run connect_to_existing(store, new_entity) from CE-CONN. Collect new connections created. (3) Run detect_topological_event(store, new_entity, new_connections) from CE-TOPO. TopologicalEvent enum: NewHub(entity, degree), Contradiction(entity_a, entity_b, conflicting_keywords), VoidBoundaryExtended(void_id, boundary_size), CommunityMerge(community_a, community_b), NoEvent. (4) If event \\!= NoEvent, run compile_micro_hypothesis(event, store, temperature) from CE-STEER. The micro-hypothesis is: for NewHub -> 'N unexplored connections. Top: {bridge_question}', for Contradiction -> 'This CONFLICTS with {other_obs}. {falsification_question}', for VoidBoundary -> 'You mapped the boundary of {area}. What is inside? {exploration_question}', for CommunityMerge -> 'Your observations about {A} and {B} are now connected through {shared_keywords}. {bridge_question}'. (5) Record micro-hypothesis in hypothesis ledger: :hypothesis/micro-{hash} with :hypothesis/trigger (the observation entity), :hypothesis/phrasing-pattern, :hypothesis/predicted-delta-fs. (6) Include micro-hypothesis text in observe command output after the standard 'observed: ...' line. Format: '-> {micro_hypothesis_text}' on a new line. (7) If no event: standard output (no forced micro-hypothesis). (8) The micro-hypothesis MUST reference at least one keyword from an existing observation (latent space coherence). ACCEPTANCE: (A) After observation that creates 2+ connections: response includes micro-hypothesis. (B) After observation that contradicts existing observation: response flags contradiction with H1 warning. (C) After observation that extends void boundary: response suggests void exploration. (D) After observation with no connections: standard output (no micro-hypothesis). (E) Micro-hypothesis references keywords from existing observations. (F) Micro-hypothesis recorded in hypothesis ledger. (G) No performance regression: observe completes in <2s including responsive analysis. DEPENDS-ON: CE-CONN (auto-connection), CE-TOPO (topological events), CE-STEER (hypothesis compilation). FILE: crates/braid/src/commands/observe.rs (responsive_observation) + crates/braid-kernel/src/connections.rs (detect_topological_event)"
